ussia-election-with-88-of-vote-show-early-results%2Famp_articleshow%2F108569153.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fputin-leads-russia-election-with-88-of-vote-show-early-results%2Famp_articleshow%2F108569153.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Putin%20Wins%20Russia%20Presidential%20Polls%20With%2088%25%20Votes%3A%201st%20Official%20Results%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPresident%20Vladimir%20Putin%20won%20a%20record%20post-Soviet%20landslide%20in%20Russia's%20election%20on%20Sunday%2C%20cementing%20his%20grip%20on%20power%20though%20thousands%20of%20opponents%20staged%20a%20noon%20protest%20at%20polling%20stations%20and%20the%20United%20States%20said%20the%20vote%20was%20neither%20free%20nor%20fair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Putin%2C%20a%20former%20KGB%20lieutenant%20colonel%20who%20first%20rose%20to%20power%20in%201999%2C%20the%20result%20is%20intended%20to%20underscore%20to%20the%20West%20that%20its%20leaders%20will%20have%20to%20reckon%20with%20an%20emboldened%20Russia%2C%20whether%20in%20war%20or%20in%20peace%2C%20for%20many%20more%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20early%20result%20means%20Putin%2C%2071%2C%20will%20easily%20secure%20a%20new%20six-year%20term%20that%20would%20enable%20him%20to%20overtake%20Josef%20Stalin%20and%20become%20Russia's%20longest-serving%20leader%20for%20more%20than%20200%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%20won%2087.8%25%20of%20the%20vote%2C%20the%20highest-ever%20result%20in%20Russia's%20post-Soviet%20history%2C%20according%20to%20an%20exit%20poll%20by%20pollster%20the%20Public%20Opinion%20Foundation%20(FOM).%20The%20Russian%20Public%20Opinion%20Research%20Centre%20(VCIOM)%20put%20Putin%20on%2087%25.%20The%20first%20official%20results%20indicated%20the%20polls%20were%20accurate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20elections%20are%20obviously%20not%20free%20nor%20fair%20given%20how%20Mr.%20Putin%20has%20imprisoned%20political%20opponents%20and%20prevented%20others%20from%20running%20against%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20White%20House's%20National%20Security%20Council%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20comes%20just%20over%20two%20years%20since%20Putin%20triggered%20the%20deadliest%20European%20conflict%20since%20World%20War%20Two%20by%20ordering%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20He%20casts%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20military%20operation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWar%20has%20hung%20over%20the%20three-day%20election%3A%20Ukraine%20has%20repeatedly%20attacked%20oil%20refineries%20in%20Russia%2C%20shelled%20Russian%20regions%20and%20sought%20to%20pierce%20Russian%20borders%20with%20proxy%20forces%20-%20a%20move%20Putin%20said%20would%20not%20be%20left%20unpunished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Putin's%20re-election%20was%20not%20in%20doubt%20given%20his%20control%20over%20Russia%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20real%20challengers%2C%20the%20former%20KGB%20spy%20wanted%20to%20show%20that%20he%20has%20the%20overwhelming%20support%20of%20Russians.%20Nationwide%20turnout%20was%2074.22%25%20at%201800%20GMT%20when%20polls%20closed%2C%20election%20officials%20said%2C%20surpassing%202018%20levels%20of%2067.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupporters%20of%20Putin's%20most%20prominent%20opponent%2C%20Alexei%20Navalny%2C%20who%20died%20in%20an%20Arctic%20prison%20last%20month%2C%20had%20called%20on%20Russians%20to%20come%20out%20at%20a%20%26quot%3BNoon%20against%20Putin%26quot%3B%20protest%20to%20show%20their%20dissent%20against%20a%20leader%20they%20describe%20as%20a%20corrupt%20autocrat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20independent%20tally%20of%20how%20many%20of%20Russia's%20114%20million%20voters%20took%20part%20in%20the%20opposition%20demonstrations%2C%20amid%20extremely%20tight%20security%20involving%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20police%20and%20security%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20journalists%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20flow%20of%20voters%2C%20especially%20younger%20people%2C%20at%20noon%20at%20polling%20stations%20in%20Moscow%2C%20St%20Petersburg%20and%20Yekaterinburg%2C%20with%20queues%20of%20several%20hundred%20people%20and%20even%20thousands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20said%20they%20were%20protesting%2C%20though%20there%20were%20few%20outward%20signs%20to%20distinguish%20them%20from%20ordinary%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20noon%20arrived%20across%20Asia%20and%20Europe%2C%20crowds%20hundreds%20strong%20gathered%20at%20polling%20stations%20at%20Russian%20diplomatic%20missions.%20Navalny's%20widow%2C%20Yulia%2C%20appeared%20at%20the%20Russian%20embassy%20in%20Berlin%20to%20cheers%20and%20chants%20of%20%26quot%3BYulia%2C%20Yulia%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExiled%20Navalny%20supporters%20broadcast%20footage%20on%20YouTube%20of%20protests%20inside%20Russia%20and%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'People%20saw%20they%20were%20not%20alone'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20showed%20ourselves%2C%20all%20of%20Russia%20and%20the%20whole%20world%20that%20Putin%20is%20not%20Russia%20that%20Putin%20has%20seized%20power%20in%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ruslan%20Shaveddinov%20of%20Navalny's%20Anti-Corruption%20Foundation.%20%26quot%3BOur%20victory%20is%20that%20we%2C%20the%20people%2C%20defeated%20fear%2C%20we%20defeated%20solitude%20-%20many%20people%20saw%20they%20were%20not%20alone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeonid%20Volkov%2C%20an%20exiled%20Navalny%20aide%20who%20was%20attacked%20with%20a%20hammer%20last%20week%20in%20Vilnius%2C%20estimated%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20had%20come%20out%20to%20polling%20stations%20in%20Moscow%2C%20St%20Petersburg%2C%20Yekaterinburg%20and%20other%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2074%20people%20were%20arrested%20on%20Sunday%20across%20Russia%2C%20according%20to%20OVD-Info%2C%20a%20group%20that%20monitors%20crackdowns%20on%20dissent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20previous%20two%20days%2C%20there%20were%20scattered%20incidents%20of%20protest%20as%20some%20Russians%20set%20fire%20to%20voting%20booths%20or%20poured%20green%20dye%20into%20ballot%20boxes.%20Russian%20officials%20called%20them%20scumbags%20and%20traitors.%20Opponents%20posted%20some%20pictures%20of%20ballots%20spoiled%20with%20slogans%20insulting%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Navalny's%20death%20has%20left%20the%20opposition%20deprived%20of%20its%20most%20formidable%20leader%2C%20and%20other%20major%20opposition%20figures%20are%20abroad%2C%20in%20jail%20or%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20West%20casts%20Putin%20as%20an%20autocrat%20and%20a%20killer.%20U.S.%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20last%20month%20dubbed%20him%20a%20%26quot%3Bcrazy%20SOB%26quot%3B.%20The%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20in%20the%20Hague%20has%20indicted%20him%20for%20the%20alleged%20war%20crime%20of%20abducting%20Ukrainian%20children%2C%20which%20the%20Kremlin%20denies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskiy%20said%20on%20Sunday%20that%20Putin%20wanted%20to%20rule%20forever.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20legitimacy%20in%20this%20imitation%20of%20elections%20and%20there%20cannot%20be.%20This%20person%20should%20be%20on%20trial%20in%20The%20Hague.%20That's%20what%20we%20have%20to%20ensure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%20portrays%20the%20war%20as%20part%20of%20a%20centuries-old%20battle%20with%20a%20declining%20and%20decadent%20West%20that%20he%20says%20humiliated%20Russia%20after%20the%20Cold%20War%20by%20encroaching%20on%20Moscow's%20sphere%20of%20influence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPutin's%20task%20is%20now%20to%20imprint%20his%20worldview%20indelibly%20into%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20Russian%20political%20establishment%26quot%3B%20to%20ensure%20a%20like-minded%20successor%2C%20Nikolas%20Gvosdev%2C%20director%20of%20the%20National%20Security%20Program%20at%20the%20Philadelphia-based%20Foreign%20Policy%20Research%20Institute%2C%20told%20the%20Russia%20Matters%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20U.S.%20administration%20that%20ho