%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20new%20player%20is%20emerging%3A%20fat%20droplets.%20But%20this%20debate%20ignores%20the%20fact%20that%20fat%20droplets%20can%20also%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20brains%20of%20people%20who%20have%20died%20from%20the%20disease%2C%20says%20Mr%20Haney.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMichael%20Haney%20investigated%20the%20APOE%20gene%2C%20a%20major%20risk%20factor%20for%20Alzheimer's.%20This%20gene%20controls%20how%20fat%20moves%20in%20and%20out%20of%20cells.%20Different%20versions%20(APOE2%2C%203%2C%20and%204)%20exist%2C%20with%20APOE4%20carrying%20the%20highest%20Alzheimer's%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Haney's%20team%20analyzed%20brain%20cells%20from%20dead%20Alzheimer's%20patients%20with%20either%20APOE4%20or%20APOE3.%20They%20found%20immune%20cells%20in%20APOE4%20brains%20produced%20more%20of%20an%20enzyme%20that%20boosted%20fat%20storage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20grew%20immune%20brain%20cells%20(microglia)%20from%20people%20with%20APOE4%20and%20APOE3.%20Exposing%20these%20cells%20to%20amyloid%20(another%20Alzheimer's%20suspect)%20increased%20fat%20build-up%2C%20especially%20in%20APOE4%20cells.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20propose%20that%20amyloid%20buildup%20triggers%20fat%20accumulation%20in%20immune%20cells.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20leads%20to%20tau%20tangles%20in%20neurons%2C%20causing%20cell%20death%20and%20memory%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenes%20linked%20to%20a%20slightly%20increased%20Alzheimer's%20risk%20often%20affect%20fat%20metabolism%20or%20the%20immune%20system%2C%20strengthening%20the%20fat%20droplet%20theory.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710694140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fdh9t16l8_brain-generic_625x300_17_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Ffat-deposits-in-brain-cells-may-cause-alzheimers-study-5257753%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Michael%20Haney%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%20said%20that%20targeting%20these%2