tary%20Dattatreya%20Hosabale%20on%20Sunday%20(March%2017)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-is-an-experiment-rss-general-secretary-dattatreya-hosabale-101710667420950.html%5C%22%3Edefended%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20declared%20unconstitutional%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20last%20month%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20is%20just%20an%20%E2%80%9Cexperiment%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cquestions%20are%20raised%20when%20a%20new%20thing%20comes%20up%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20that%20electoral%20bonds%20have%20suddenly%20been%20introduced%20today%2C%20it%20(such%20scheme)%20was%20brought%20earlier%20also.%20Whenever%20a%20change%20is%20introduced%2C%20questions%20are%20raised.%20Questions%20were%20also%20raised%20when%20the%20EVMs%20(electronic%20voting%20machines)%20were%20introduced%E2%80%A6It%20is%20natural%2C%E2%80%9D%20Hosabale%2C%20who%20was%20speaking%20to%20the%20media%20after%20an%20annual%20meeting%20of%20RSS%E2%80%99%20apex%20decision-making%20body%20in%20Nagpur%2C%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20time%20will%20tell%20how%20beneficial%20and%20effective%20the%20new%20system%20is.%20So%2C%20we%20should%20allow%20such%20experiments%20to%20take%20place.%20That%20is%20the%20Sangh%E2%80%99s%20view%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20was%20quoted%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Felectoral-bonds-is-an-experiment-rss-general-secretary-dattatreya-hosabale-101710667420950.html%5C%22%3Esaying%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20on%20Sunday%20released%20fresh%20data%20that%20was%20submitted%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover.%20On%20Thursday%2C%20EC%20had%20released%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)-provided%20data%20on%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20on%20its%20website%2C%20in%20compliance%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20directive.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20received%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%206%2C060.5%20crore%20in%20electoral%20bonds%20making%20it%20the%20largest%20recipient%20of%20these%20%E2%80%98anonymous%E2%80%99%20donations%20by%20a%20large%20margin%20compared%20to%20all%20other%20national%20and%20regional%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20letter%20to%20the%20EC%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20sealed%20cover%20data%20unveiled%20by%20the%20commission%20on%20its%20website%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20said%20that%20as%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20required%20to%20maintain%20the%20names%20and%20particulars%20of%20the%20donors%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20and%20as%20such%20the%20Party%20has%20not%20maintained%20these%20particulars%E2%80%9D.%20Consequently%2C%20the%20donors%E2%80%99%20names%20are%20not%20listed%20but%20the%20bonds%20encashed%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710689097000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F17205300%2FCopy-of-Copy-of-Lead-image-size-8.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fjust-an-experiment-time-will-tell-how-beneficial-they-are-rss-gen-sec-defends-electoral-bonds%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWhenever%20a%20change%20is%20introduced%2C%20questions%20are%20raised.%20Questions%20were%20also%20raised%20when%20the%20EVMs%20(electronic%20voting%20machines)%20were%20introduced%2C%26quot%3B%20RSS%20general%20secretary%20Dattatreya%20Hosabale%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fjust-an-experiment-time-will-tell-how-beneficial-they-are-rss-gen-sec-defends-electoral-bonds%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BIf%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Are%20Not%20There...%26quot%3B%3A%20Nitin%20Gadkari%20Points%20Out%20Drawback%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EUnion%20minister%20Nitin%20Gadkari%20today%20said%20that%20the%20scrapping%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20scheme%20would%20open%20the%20gates%20for%20black%20money%20and%20all%20parties%20should%20think%20about%20developing%20a%20better%20system.%20In%20an%20exclusive%20interview%20with%20NDTV%20Editor-in-Chief%20Sanjay%20Pugalia%2C%20Mr%20Gadkari%20supported%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20that%20was%20developed%20when%20the%20late%20Arun%20Jaitley%20was%20the%20country's%20finance%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20fact%20that%20money%20is%20needed%20to%20contest%20elections.%20Every%20party%20needs%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20scheme%20was%20made%20with%20the%20idea%20that%20parties%20would%20get%20money%20through%20bonds%20and%20it%20will%20help%20push%20the%20economy%20if%20you%20want%20to%20make%20it%20number%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Gadkari%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20Prime%C2%A0%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20ambitions%20on%20the%20economic%20front.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20was%20wrong%20with%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20questioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeclaring%20that%20he%20would%20not%20comment%20on%20a%20decision%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Mr%20Gadkari%2C%20however%2C%20pointed%20out%20another%20drawback%20of%20a%20ban.%20If%20electoral%20bonds%20are%20banned%2C%20money%20would%20still%20come%20in%2C%20only%20in%20the%20form%20of%20black%20money%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20you%20do%20not%20allow%20(electoral)%20bonds%2C%20people%20will%20take%20money%20as%20number%20two.%20This%20will%20happen%20anyway%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20scrapped%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%2C%20objecting%20to%20the%20unlimited%20and%20undisclosed%20funding%20through%20corporate%20donations%20that%20come%20with%20strings%20attached.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPolitical%20contributors%20get%20access...%20this%20access%20leads%20to%20policy%20making...%20because%20of%20the%20nexus%20between%20money%20and%20voting.%20Financial%20supports%20to%20political%20parties%20can%20lead%20to%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangement%2C%26quot%3B%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20Chandrachud%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Gadkari%20pointed%20out%20that%20electoral%20bonds%20%26quot%3Bwill%20be%20purchased%20by%20people%20who%20are%20wealthy%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20wealthy%20would%20be%20contractors.%20Or%20have%20made%20it%20big%20in%20trade%20or%20industry.%20So%20it%20is%20not%20right%20to%20link%20it%20to%20that%20(quid%20pro%20quo)%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20was%20pointed%20out%20that%20electoral%20bonds%20can%20bring%20black%20money%20into%20the%20system%2C%20Mr%20Gadkari%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20can%20money%20that%20create%20growth%2C%20and%20generate%20employment%20and%20revenue%20be%20called%20black%20money%3F%20The%20problem%20is%20money%20that%20is%20taken%20outside%20the%20country%20and%20dumped%20elsewhere%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20had%20called%20the%20Electoral%20Bonds%20scheme%20unconstitutional%2C%20saying%20information%20about%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%20is%20essential%20to%20make%20electoral%20choices%20since%20the%20system%20leads%20to%20tweaking%20of%20the%20country's%20policies%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20donor.%20While%20Indian%20election%20system%20involves%20secret%20ballot%2C%20the%20cloak%20of%20anonymity%20cannot%20be%20extended%20to%20political%20donations%20above%20the%20Rs%202000%20threshold%2C%20the%20court%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710688800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2F2nonlfd_gadkari-1200_650x400_17_March_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fif-electoral-bonds-are-not-there-nitin-gadkari-points-out-drawback-5257329%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Union%20minister%20Nitin%2